<section>
    <h3>The Image Scraper Microservice is also available as a RESTful API.</h3>
    <p>
        Simply send a request to the following address: <br>
        <mark>http://flip3.engr.oregonstate.edu:3082/api?searchTerm=[your search term]</mark><br>
        This will get an unpixelated version of the image at its original resolution.
    </p>
    <p>
        Specify additional <b>optional</b> parameters by including:
        <ul>
            <li>
                &width=[integer width in pixels] or &height=[integer height in pixels]
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Include only one of the two dimensions (defaults to width if both dimensions are included). The resulting image will be scaled to the specified dimension.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                &pixelation=[integer from 0 to 199]
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Setting this to 0 will result in no pixelation while 199 will produce an extremely pixelated image. The default setting is 0.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
        You'll receive a URL to your image in JSON.
    </p>
    <p>
        For example, request <mark>http://flip3.engr.oregonstate.edu:3082/api?searchTerm=apple&width=500</mark> and you'll receive:<br>
        {<br>
            "searchTerm":"apple",<br>
            "fileName":"Malus_domestica_a1.jpg",<br>
            "url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/22/Malus_domestica_a1.jpg/500px-Malus_domestica_a1.jpg",<br>
            "width":500,<br>
            "height":373,<br>
            "descriptionURL":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Malus_domestica_a1.jpg",<br>
            "artist":"Opio≈Ça Jerzy (Poland)",<br>
            "licenseShortName":"CC BY 2.5",<br>
            "title":"Malus domestica a1",<br>
            "pixelation": 0<br>
        }
    </p>
</section>